---
import SidebarLayout from '../../../layouts/SidebarLayout.astro';
import "../../../styles/global.css";
---

<SidebarLayout app="css">
  <h1 class="text-xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-5 text-custom-accent text-center">
    Position Property
  </h1>

  <section class="mb-5 space-y-6 text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed text-custom-secondary">
    <p>
      The CSS position property determines how an element is positioned in the document. It's essential for creating overlays, fixed navigation, and complex layouts.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mt-6 mb-3">Position Values</h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="min-w-full border-collapse border border-custom text-sm sm:text-base">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-custom-secondary">
            <th class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2 text-custom-primary">Value</th>
            <th class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2 text-custom-primary">Description</th>
            <th class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2 text-custom-primary">Use Case</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-custom-secondary">
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">static</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Default position in normal flow</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Regular document flow</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">relative</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Positioned relative to its normal position</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Minor adjustments, z-index context</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">absolute</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Positioned relative to nearest positioned ancestor</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Overlays, tooltips, custom controls</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">fixed</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Positioned relative to viewport</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Fixed headers, modals, chat widgets</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">sticky</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Toggles between relative and fixed based on scroll</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Sticky headers, table headers</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mt-6 mb-3">Position Examples</h2>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-lg p-3 sm:p-4 my-4">
      <pre class="text-xs sm:text-sm overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre-wrap"><code>{`/* Relative positioning */
.relative-box {
  position: relative;
  top: 10px;
  left: 20px;
}

/* Absolute positioning */
.absolute-box {
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  right: 0;
}

/* Fixed positioning */
.fixed-header {
  position: fixed;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100%;
  z-index: 1000;
}

/* Sticky positioning */
.sticky-element {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
}`}</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6 mt-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mb-3">Key Concepts</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-4">
        <li><strong class="text-custom-primary">z-index</strong> controls stacking order of positioned elements</li>
        <li>Absolute elements are positioned relative to their nearest positioned ancestor</li>
        <li>Fixed elements don't move when the page scrolls</li>
        <li>Sticky elements need a threshold value (top, bottom, etc.)</li>
        <li>Positioned elements create a new stacking context</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</SidebarLayout>